# Line-ending policy: text files normalize to LF in the repo and check
# out as LF on every platform. The cross-platform CRLF round-trip on
# Windows was triggering "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings on every
# commit (and producing those warnings as noise in tooling output) even
# though the working tree contents were already correct. Locking eol=lf
# stops the dance.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Keep Windows-native files as CRLF — batch scripts and PowerShell
# break under LF on some Windows shells.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Treat these as binary so git doesn't try to munge bytes.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.dmg binary
*.exe binary
*.lockb binary

# Lockfiles are large and machine-generated. Git will still diff them
# (linguist-detectable=false isn't applicable here) but mark them as
# generated so GitHub's diff view collapses them by default and they
# don't dominate the language stats / contributor graph.
package-lock.json linguist-generated
yarn.lock linguist-generated
pnpm-lock.yaml linguist-generated
src-tauri/Cargo.lock linguist-generated
